he </div><div class="t m189 x74 h2d yde2 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">body of a fish, and the head and hands of a man. </div><div class="t m1d5 x74 h2d yd97 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">When the idol fell before the ark and lost his head </div><div class="t m1343 x74 h2d y7d8 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and his hands, only the fishy portion remained. </div><div class="t m3c3 x74 h2d yd98 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The record says that &quot;only Dagon was left to him.&quot; </div><div class="t m1120 x74 h2d yd99 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Now the word &quot;Dagon &quot; is the diminutive of the </div><div class="t me80 x74 h2d y1264 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Hebrew word for fish, so that we have in reality the </div><div class="t m1344 x74 h2d y1265 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">statement that when Dagon fell before the ark and </div><div class="t m120 x74 h2d yf42 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lost his head and his hands, &quot; only a little fish was </div><div class="t m3c9 x74 h2d y1266 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">left.&quot; That is all that there was to the idol in which </div><div class="t m41c x74 h2d y1267 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the Philistines trusted. </div><div class="t m283 xb h8 y93a ff4 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">r__,]Essco </div><div class="t m1345 x2f h2d y93a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">INT IX. </div><div class="t m1d8 x6b h25 y9c3 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOVEMBER 29, 1890. </div><div class="t m1346 x40 h13 ya08 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">DESIRING A KING. </div><div class="t m1347 x5b h4a y9fc ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Read &quot;Patriarchs and Prophets, pp. 60</div><div class="t m6ec x54 h4a y9fc ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3</div><div class="t m1348 x46 h4a y9fc ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">-608.) </div><div class="t m7b0 x34 h2d ya21 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">I. WHAT did Samuel do when he was old? </div><div class="t mae1 x73 h2d yd68 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sam. 8: I. </div><div class="t m127 xc5 h2d y942 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m2c9 x49 h2d y942 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 l